# Semiotic UI Pattern

Use visual symbols (icons, colors, animations) instead of text labels to reduce localization overhead and create universally understandable interfaces.

## Core Principle

**Icons communicate state, not text.**

## Loading States

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Text requires translation
<div>
  <Loader className="w-5 h-5 animate-spin" />
  <span>Loading entries...</span>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Icon only
<div className="flex items-center justify-center h-32">
  <Loader className="w-5 h-5 text-purple-500 animate-spin" />
</div>

// ✅ ACCEPTABLE - For accessibility (use aria-label/title)
<div 
  className="flex items-center justify-center h-32"
  aria-label="Loading content"
  role="status"
>
  <Loader className="w-5 h-5 text-purple-500 animate-spin" />
</div>
```

## Error States

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div>
  <AlertCircle className="w-5 h-5 text-red-500" />
  <span>Failed to load</span>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Icon color communicates error
<div className="flex items-center justify-center" title="Error">
  <AlertCircle className="w-6 h-6 text-red-500" />
</div>
```

## Empty States

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div>
  <FileText className="w-12 h-12 text-gray-300" />
  <p>No entries available</p>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Icon with subtle styling indicates empty state
<div className="flex items-center justify-center h-full">
  <FileText className="w-16 h-16 text-gray-300 opacity-60" />
</div>
```

## Success States

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div>
  <CheckCircle2 className="w-5 h-5 text-green-600" />
  <span>Download complete!</span>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Animated icon communicates success
<div>
  <CheckCircle2 className="w-5 h-5 text-green-600 animate-pulse" />
</div>
```

## Progress Indicators

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div>
  <span>Downloading 5 of 10 items...</span>
  <ProgressBar value={50} />
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Visual progress with percentage badge
<div>
  <div className="relative">
    <Download className="w-5 h-5" />
    <span className="absolute -top-1 -right-1 bg-blue-600 text-white text-xs px-1 rounded-full">
      50%
    </span>
  </div>
</div>
```

## When Text is Necessary

Use `title`, `aria-label`, or `aria-describedby` attributes for accessibility:

```tsx
<button
  onClick={handleSave}
  title="Save changes"
  aria-label="Save changes"
>
  <Save className="w-5 h-5" />
</button>
```

## Visual Communication Hierarchy

1. **Icon shape** - Conveys action/state type
2. **Color** - Indicates status (red=error, green=success, blue=info)
3. **Animation** - Shows activity (spin, pulse, bounce)
4. **Size** - Emphasizes importance
5. **Opacity** - Communicates availability/relevance
